#TamadaMedia #Wirally
Software Employees and their struggles with their managers.. It's a never ending saga! Pressure cooker is the story of an IT employee Manasa and the pressure she faces in her office with her sinister manager.

Cast: Jaiyetri Makana, Chaitanya Varma, Vamsi krishna lingala, Prakash Jai, Sunandini, Vasanthi,
Kanuri Lakshmikantamani, Annam Krishna Karthik.Manneru Saiteja, Sesh Karthikeya,Pranitha Tejaswini.
Directed By: Vamsi Krishna Lingala
Produced by: Saideep Reddy Borra, Rahul Tamada.
Executive Producer: Anil Kumar Prattipati

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. Are you ready for the challenge?

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. snippet.description:

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCDnq05Q89oYq-Tz5boL73Tw/join

I was the first guest at Yuvraj Singh‚Äôs first-ever restaurant, Koca, in Gurugram ‚Äî and it wasn‚Äôt just about delicious food. This episode is packed with heartwarming, inspiring, and unheard stories straight from Yuvraj‚Äôs life.

I sat down for an intimate conversation with Yuvraj Singh and his mother, Shabnam Singh, where she opened up like never before. From adorable childhood memories of Yuvi, his rebellious streak, and the challenges of raising a champion, to their family‚Äôs struggle during his battle with cancer ‚Äî she shared it all.

We also spoke about Yuvraj‚Äôs journey to cricket stardom, his equation with his father Yograj Singh, her parenting style as a single mother, and for the first time, how she was introduced to her daughter-in-law Hazel Keech. It‚Äôs a candid, emotional and joyful episode you don‚Äôt want to miss!

And of course, you‚Äôll get an exclusive tour of Koca, where Yuvi takes me through his favorite dishes and the story behind launching his dream restaurant.

From the secret behind her legendary Kadhi Chawal, to Yuvraj‚Äôs most emotional cricket moments, his battle with cancer, love life with Hazel Keech and becoming a dad at 40, nothing is off the table!


Hit play, join us for this special brunch, and don‚Äôt forget to like, comment, and subscribe!
